race.comment: Some likely types engaged and it's competitive. PRIVATEER (6) is up and running and second-up led and was narrowly beaten over 1200m at Seymour. The speed bred filly has the blinkers applied for the first time and Ben Melham is aboard today. In a top barn and she should manage the longer sprint. ALL TOO SINGLE (1) settled back and dug deep to miss by a half-length over 1300m at Sandown Hillside. Hard fit and Newitt will give her every chance from the handy gate. Is sure to appreciate the extra metres. OTTOLENGHI (5) resumes and two back she was beaten just 1.3L at Seymour behind the handy Ruska Roma on a heavy track. Will race on the dry today but the form is there. Has jumped out well and maps for a soft run. SILENT ANSWER (8) and SEYCHELLES (7) both resume and have shown enough to take seriously.
